# Slack Surface

## Quick Reference

- `slack.json` at workspace root configures the Slack app (always present, `{"enabled": false}` by default)
- `ctx.notify.slack({ to, message, blocks?, thread_ts? })` — send messages
- `ctx.slack.updateMessage({ channel, ts, text?, blocks? })` — update messages after actions
- `ctx.slack.openModal({ triggerId, view })` — open modals from slash commands
- `ctx.slack.updateModal({ viewId, view })` — update open modals (multi-step flows)
- Modal submission: `ctx.params.formValues` (form data), `ctx.params.metadata` (private_metadata), `ctx.params.viewId`
- Action ID convention: `mug:<workflow>:<action>` routes button clicks and modal submissions to workflows
- `ctx.waitForUrl("event")` — generates callback URLs for approval buttons

## slack.json Configuration

```json
{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "Acme Dispatch",
  "description": "Job dispatch and approval",
  "color": "#1a1a2e",
  "botName": "acme-ops",
  "homeTab": {
    "enabled": true,
    "sections": [
      { "type": "text", "title": "Dashboard", "text": "Real-time overview." },
      { "type": "query", "title": "Active Jobs", "database": "jobs", "query": "SELECT title, status FROM jobs WHERE status = 'active'", "columns": ["title", "status"] },
      { "type": "actions", "buttons": [{ "text": "Run Report", "workflow": "daily-report", "style": "primary" }] },
      { "type": "divider" }
    ]
  },
  "messagesTab": true,
  "shortcuts": [
    { "name": "Create Dispatch", "callbackId": "create_dispatch", "description": "Create a new job", "type": "global", "workflow": "create-dispatch" }
  ],
  "unfurlDomains": ["acme.mug.work"]
}
```

Scopes auto-inferred. Always: `chat:write`, `channels:join`, `channels:read`, `groups:read`, `users:read`, `users:read.email`, `im:write`, `mpim:read`, `mpim:write`, `reactions:write`, `files:write`. Shortcuts add `commands`, chat agents add `assistant:write`.

## Workflow Triggers (in .ts files, not slack.json)

```typescript
import { workflow } from "@mugwork/mug";

workflow("handle-dispatch", async (ctx) => {
  await ctx.slack.openModal({ triggerId: ctx.params.triggerId, view: { ... } });
}, {
  trigger: { type: "slack_command", command: "/dispatch", description: "Create a dispatch" },
});
```

## Key Patterns

`ctx.notify.slack({ to })` — `to` accepts `#channel-name`, `channel-name`, or channel ID. Names resolve automatically. Bot auto-joins public channels; private channels need manual invite via Integrations tab.

**Send Block Kit message with action buttons:**
```typescript
await ctx.notify.slack({
  to: channelId,
  message: "Fallback text",
  blocks: [
    { type: "section", text: { type: "mrkdwn", text: "*Title*\nDetails here" } },
    { type: "actions", elements: [
      { type: "button", text: { type: "plain_text", text: "Approve" }, action_id: "mug:handler:approve", value: id, style: "primary" },
    ] },
  ],
});
```

**Handle button click (in the routed workflow):**
```typescript
// ctx.params.actionId = "approve", ctx.params.actionValue = id
await ctx.slack.updateMessage({
  channel: ctx.params.channelId,
  ts: ctx.params.messageTs,
  text: "Done",
});
```

**Modal forms — open from slash command, handle submission in same workflow:**
```typescript
workflow("create-job", async (ctx) => {
  if (ctx.params.type === "slash_command") {
    await ctx.slack.openModal({
      triggerId: ctx.params.triggerId,
      view: {
        type: "modal",
        callback_id: "mug:create-job:submit",
        private_metadata: JSON.stringify({ channelId: ctx.params.channelId }),
        title: { type: "plain_text", text: "New Job" },
        submit: { type: "plain_text", text: "Create" },
        blocks: [
          { type: "input", block_id: "title_block", label: { type: "plain_text", text: "Title" },
            element: { type: "plain_text_input", action_id: "title" } },
          { type: "input", block_id: "priority_block", label: { type: "plain_text", text: "Priority" },
            element: { type: "static_select", action_id: "priority", options: [
              { text: { type: "plain_text", text: "Low" }, value: "low" },
              { text: { type: "plain_text", text: "High" }, value: "high" },
            ] } },
        ],
      },
    });
  }
  if (ctx.params.type === "view_submission") {
    const v = ctx.params.formValues;
    const title = v?.title_block?.title?.value;
    const priority = v?.priority_block?.priority?.selected_option?.value;
    const meta = JSON.parse(ctx.params.metadata || "{}");
    await ctx.notify.slack({ to: meta.channelId, message: `Job created: ${title} (${priority})` });
  }
}, { trigger: { type: "slack_command", command: "/newjob", description: "Create a job" } });
```

**Dynamic select menus** — for large datasets (100+ options), use `external_select` + `suggestions` in slack.json:
```json
{ "suggestions": { "customer-picker": { "database": "crm", "query": "SELECT name, id FROM customers WHERE name LIKE ? LIMIT 20" } } }
```
Action_id on the select block must match the key. User's typed text passed as `%value%` LIKE param. First column = display, second = value.

**Update modal (multi-step):** `await ctx.slack.updateModal({ viewId: ctx.params.viewId, view: { ... } })`

**Home Tab sections:** query (run SQL → table), actions (buttons → workflows), text (header + markdown), divider.

**Slack data (auto-synced):** `slack_users` (user_id, email, display_name), `slack_channels` (channel_id, name)

## App Setup

`mug slack setup` supports flag-driven mode for AI agents — no readline prompts needed.

**Check state:** `mug slack setup --json` — returns `appId`, `hasCredentials`, `hasConfigToken`, `configTokenValid`, `hasBotToken`, `hasAgents`, plus relevant URLs.

**New app (admin):** check state → open `https://api.slack.com/apps` for user → user copies config tokens → `mug slack setup --config-token "..." --refresh-token "..."` → `mug slack setup --create-app` → `mug slack setup --install-url --open`

**New app (not admin):** `mug slack setup --admin-instructions` outputs copy-pasteable instructions with manifest JSON for the user to send to their Slack admin → admin sends back 6 values → `mug slack setup --app-id "..." --client-id "..." --client-secret "..." --signing-secret "..."` → `mug slack setup --config-token "..." --refresh-token "..."` → `mug slack setup --install-url --open`

**Refresh expired token:** check state (look for `configTokenValid: false`) → open `https://api.slack.com/apps` for user → user copies fresh tokens → `mug slack setup --config-token "..." --refresh-token "..."`

**Reinstall (scope changes):** `mug slack setup --install-url --open`

**Other flags:** `--manifest` (output manifest JSON), `--install-url` (print install URL), `--install-url --open` (print and open)

After setup: `mug deploy` (push manifest) → share install URL → bot token auto-stored on OAuth callback.

## AI Agent DMs (Agents & AI Apps)

Set `"chat": true` in `agent.json` + `"defaultAgent"` in `slack.json` → threaded AI conversations via Slack's Agents & AI Apps.

```json
// slack.json
{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "Acme Ops",
  "defaultAgent": "ops-bot",
  "suggestedPrompts": [
    { "title": "Ask Ops Bot", "agent": "ops-bot" },
    { "title": "Check Schedule", "message": "What's on the schedule today?" }
  ],
  "appIcon": "assets/slack-icon.png"  // reference only — upload manually via Slack UI
}
```

```json
// agents/ops-bot/agent.json
{
  "model": "openai/gpt-4.1-nano",
  "tools": ["query"],
  "chat": true,
  "slackName": "ops-bot"
}
```

**Multi-agent routing:** suggested prompt clicks pin thread to agent. @mentions route by `slackName`. Thread stays pinned to one agent.

**After first deploy with chat agents:** enable "Agents & AI Apps" toggle and set suggested prompts to "Dynamic" at `https://api.slack.com/apps/<app_id>/app-assistant`. `mug deploy` prints the link.
